{"id":"reproduction-8","label":"Reproduction in Animals","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Binary fission is observed in","options":"Amoeba, Hydra, Yeast, Human Being"},{"qText":"Asexual reproduction is observed in","options":"Sponge, Cow, Buffalo, Hen"},{"qText":"In Hydra, the type of reproduction is ","options":"asexual, sexual, * both, none"},{"qText":"The animals that produce new young ones are called","options":"viviparous, oviparous"},{"qText":"Ovum or egg is formed in","options":"ovary, testis, penis, oviduct"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"In humans, the development of fertilised egg takes place in the","options":"uterus, ovary, oviduct, testis"},{"qText":"The cell formed after fertilisation is called","options":"Zygote, Ovary, Uterus, Testis"},{"qText":"The fusion of sperm and ova usually occur in the","options":"oviduct, uterus, ovary, testis"},{"qText":"Which of the following undergo external fertilisation?","options":"Frog, Human Being, Cow, Hen"},{"qText":"Animals exhibiting external fertilisation produce a large number of gametes. Why?","options":"To ensure better chance of fertilisation\n        The animals are small in size and want to produce more offsprings\n        Food is available in plenty in water\n        Water promotes production of large number of gametes"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which is not a viviparous animal?","options":"Butterfly, Human being, Cow, Dog"},{"qText":"Budding occurs in","options":"Yeast and Hydra, Paramecium, Dog, Amoeba"},{"qText":"The female gamete is called","options":"ova, sperm, zygote, uterus"},{"qText":"The male gamete is called","options":"sperm, ova, embryo, zygote"},{"qText":"Reproduction is essential for living organisms in order to","options":"continue their species\n        fulfil their energy requirement\n        maintain growth\n        keep the individual organism alive"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"The number of eggs produced in internal fertilisation is ____ external fertilisation.","options":"less than,  more than,  equal to"},{"qText":"After fertilisation, the _____ divides repeatedly to give rise to a ball of cells.","options":"zygote, embryo, ovum, sperm"},{"qText":"Which of the following is not a part of male reproductive system?","options":"Ovary, Testis, Vas Deferens, Penis"},{"qText":"A paramecium reproduces by dividing itself into two daughter cells. This process is called  ______.","options":"Binary fission, Budding, Vegetative propagation, Regeneration"},{"qText":"Name the process in which tadpoles develop into young frogs.","options":"Metamorphosis, Embedding, Budding, Fertilisation"},{"qText":"The process by which organisms make copies of themselves is called ","options":"reproduction, respiration, transpiration, photosynthesis"}]}]}]}